1
00:00:07,667 --> 00:00:08,625
- EARTH.

2
00:00:08,667 --> 00:00:10,583
FIRE.

3
00:00:10,625 --> 00:00:12,542
AIR.

4
00:00:12,583 --> 00:00:14,458
WATER.

5
00:00:14,500 --> 00:00:18,875
ONLY THE AVATAR CAN MASTER
ALL FOUR ELEMENTS

6
00:00:18,917 --> 00:00:20,917
AND BRING BALANCE
TO THE WORLD.

7
00:00:20,959 --> 00:00:23,208
[dramatic music]

8
00:00:23,250 --> 00:00:24,667
♪ ♪

9
00:00:27,166 --> 00:00:28,917
- KORRA HAS REOPENED
THE SOUTHERN SPIRIT PORTAL

10
00:00:28,959 --> 00:00:31,417
AND TAKEN THE FIRST STEP
TO RESTORING BALANCE

11
00:00:31,458 --> 00:00:33,250
BETWEEN SPIRITS AND MAN.

12
00:00:33,291 --> 00:00:35,875
MEANWHILE, TENSIONS ARE HIGH
BETWEEN KORRA AND HER FATHER

13
00:00:35,917 --> 00:00:38,500
AFTER SHE DISCOVERED HE WAS
HIDING A DARK SECRET.

14
00:00:38,542 --> 00:00:40,959
YEARS AGO, TONRAQ WAS BANISHED
FROM THE NORTH.

15
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:44,125
AND NOW THE NORTHERN NAVY
HAS LANDED ON SOUTHERN SHORES.

16
00:00:44,166 --> 00:00:46,917
WHAT OTHER PLANS DOES UNALAQ
HAVE FOR THE AVATAR?

17
00:00:51,709 --> 00:00:52,917
[wind blowing]

18
00:00:52,959 --> 00:00:54,458
[people chattering]

19
00:01:00,291 --> 00:01:01,542
- EVERYONE, CLEAR THE STREETS.

20
00:01:01,583 --> 00:01:02,959
GET BACK IN YOUR HOMES.

21
00:01:03,041 --> 00:01:05,959
[suspenseful music]

22
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:08,709
♪ ♪

23
00:01:08,750 --> 00:01:10,500
[crowd gasping]

24
00:01:10,542 --> 00:01:18,208
♪ ♪

25
00:01:30,792 --> 00:01:33,625
- UNCLE, WHY DID YOU BRING
YOUR TROOPS DOWN FROM THE NORTH?

26
00:01:33,667 --> 00:01:35,834
- NOW THAT YOU'VE OPENED
THE SOUTHERN PORTAL,

27
00:01:35,875 --> 00:01:37,458
WE NEED TO PROTECT IT
FROM PEOPLE

28
00:01:37,500 --> 00:01:39,583
WHO WOULD DO
THE SPIRITS HARM.
- I CAN PROTECT IT.

29
00:01:39,625 --> 00:01:42,166
- I NEED YOU FOR SOMETHING
MORE IMPORTANT.

30
00:01:42,208 --> 00:01:45,166
THERE IS ANOTHER PORTAL
IN THE NORTH.

31
00:01:45,208 --> 00:01:48,000
ONCE YOU OPEN IT,
SPIRITS AND MAN WILL BE ABLE

32
00:01:48,041 --> 00:01:49,875
TO MOVE FREELY BETWEEN THE NORTH
AND THE SOUTH

33
00:01:49,917 --> 00:01:51,542
IN A MATTER OF SECONDS.

34
00:01:51,583 --> 00:01:53,291
- BUT THE SOLSTICE IS OVER.

35
00:01:53,333 --> 00:01:54,875
HOW AM I GOING TO OPEN IT?

36
00:01:54,917 --> 00:01:58,333
- THE SPIRITUAL ENERGY
IS MUCH STRONGER IN THE NORTH.

37
00:01:58,375 --> 00:02:00,458
AND NOW THAT YOU'VE OPENED
THE SOUTHERN PORTAL,

38
00:02:00,500 --> 00:02:03,291
YOUR ENERGY IS STRONGER
AS WELL.

39
00:02:03,333 --> 00:02:06,959
- WITH BOTH PORTALS OPEN,
OUR TRIBES WILL BE UNITED AGAIN.

40
00:02:07,000 --> 00:02:09,667
- THE WORLD WILL BE
UNITED AGAIN.

41
00:02:22,667 --> 00:02:25,625
- AHH, I HAVEN'T FELT
THIS AT PEACE SINCE--

42
00:02:25,667 --> 00:02:28,041
- WAHOO!

43
00:02:28,083 --> 00:02:29,458
- AND IT'S OVER.

44
00:02:29,500 --> 00:02:31,750
- GOOD MORNING, UNIVERSE!

45
00:02:31,792 --> 00:02:34,375
- BUMI, PLEASE.
COVER YOURSELF.

46
00:02:34,417 --> 00:02:35,917
- WELL, LOOKEE HERE.

47
00:02:35,959 --> 00:02:39,083
"VACATION TENZIN" HAS FINALLY
DECIDED TO JOIN US.

48
00:02:39,125 --> 00:02:41,792
- YES, HE HAS.

49
00:02:41,834 --> 00:02:43,792
IT'S SO NICE TO GET
TO SPEND MORE TIME

50
00:02:43,834 --> 00:02:45,250
WITH MY FAMILY.

51
00:02:45,291 --> 00:02:46,375
[baby voice]
ISN'T THAT RIGHT,

52
00:02:46,417 --> 00:02:47,959
MY LITTLE ROHAN?

53
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,709
- [coos]

54
00:02:49,750 --> 00:02:53,083
- AND I'VE REALLY ENJOYED
HAVING YOU TWO AROUND.

55
00:02:53,125 --> 00:02:54,959
REMINDS ME OF ALL THOSE
GREAT VACATIONS WE TOOK

56
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:56,500
AS KIDS WITH DAD.

57
00:02:56,542 --> 00:02:59,458
- UH, I THINK YOUR MEMORY
IS A LITTLE FOGGY.

58
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:02,125
BUMI AND I WEREN'T
ON THOSE GREAT VACATIONS.

59
00:03:02,166 --> 00:03:04,458
IT WAS ALWAYS JUST YOU
AND DAD.

60
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:06,542
- NO, THAT CAN'T BE RIGHT.

61
00:03:06,583 --> 00:03:08,500
WHAT ABOUT THE TIME HE TOOK US
TO KYOSHI ISLAND

62
00:03:08,542 --> 00:03:10,083
TO RIDE THE ELEPHANT-KOI?

63
00:03:10,125 --> 00:03:12,208
- NOPE.
WE WEREN'T THERE.

64
00:03:12,250 --> 00:03:13,750
- HMM.

65
00:03:13,792 --> 00:03:15,917
OH, REMEMBER EMBER ISLAND?

66
00:03:15,959 --> 00:03:18,917
THOSE AMAZING SAND PALACES
WE BUILT ON THE BEACH?

67
00:03:18,959 --> 00:03:20,667
- YOU MEAN YOU BUILT.

68
00:03:20,709 --> 00:03:22,083
WE NEVER SAW THE PLACE.

69
00:03:22,125 --> 00:03:24,208
- I COULD'VE SWORN--

70
00:03:24,250 --> 00:03:26,917
[laughter]

71
00:03:26,959 --> 00:03:28,375
- WOO-HOO!
- MORNING, KIDS.

72
00:03:28,417 --> 00:03:31,083
- MORNING, UNCLE BUMI.

73
00:03:31,125 --> 00:03:32,250
DO YOU HAVE A BABY IN THERE?

74
00:03:32,291 --> 00:03:35,709
[laughter]

75
00:03:35,750 --> 00:03:37,959
- WHERE'S YOUR SISTER?

76
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:39,583
- WHO?

77
00:03:39,625 --> 00:03:43,041
- IKKI. ABOUT THIS TALL.
TALKS REAL FAST.

78
00:03:43,083 --> 00:03:44,208
I'M SURE YOU KNOW HER.

79
00:03:44,250 --> 00:03:46,041
- UH...

80
00:03:46,083 --> 00:03:48,333
THERE WAS A LEMUR FIGHT,
BUT THE BISON TOLD US

81
00:03:48,375 --> 00:03:50,625
NOT TO WORRY
BECAUSE A GIANT WAS COMING.

82
00:03:50,667 --> 00:03:53,792
THEN WE ALMOST GOT EATEN
BY A SHARK-SQUID.

83
00:03:53,834 --> 00:03:56,375
- THE SHARK-SQUID?
HE'S HERE?

84
00:03:56,417 --> 00:04:00,083
IT APPEARS MY OLD NEMESIS
HAS FOUND ME.

85
00:04:00,125 --> 00:04:03,041
- JINORA, WERE YOU AND MEELO
TEASING YOUR SISTER AGAIN?

86
00:04:03,083 --> 00:04:04,750
- I DON'T KNOW.

87
00:04:04,792 --> 00:04:05,959
MAYBE.

88
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:06,959
YES.

89
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,583
[lemur purrs]

90
00:04:09,625 --> 00:04:11,500
- SHE RAN AWAY.

91
00:04:11,542 --> 00:04:15,834
- HONESTLY, I DON'T KNOW WHY
YOU KIDS CAN'T JUST GET ALONG!

92
00:04:15,875 --> 00:04:17,667
- IT'S ALL RIGHT, DEAR.

93
00:04:17,709 --> 00:04:20,375
IKKI COULDN'T HAVE GONE FAR.
I'LL FIND HER.

94
00:04:20,417 --> 00:04:22,709
- COMMANDER BUMI
REPORTING FOR DUTY!

95
00:04:22,750 --> 00:04:25,625
SEARCH-AND-RESCUE MISSIONS
ARE MY SPECIALTY.

96
00:04:25,667 --> 00:04:28,333
- WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE ALL GO TOGETHER?

97
00:04:28,375 --> 00:04:30,417
- SURE.
I COULD USE THE HELP.

98
00:04:30,458 --> 00:04:32,458
- WHEN I GET BACK,
WE'LL COME UP WITH A PLAN

99
00:04:32,500 --> 00:04:36,291
TO TAKE DOWN THAT SHARK-SQUID
ONCE AND FOR ALL.

100
00:04:36,333 --> 00:04:40,875
- YEAH!

101
00:04:40,917 --> 00:04:42,917
- THANK YOU FOR COMING,
EVERYONE.

102
00:04:42,959 --> 00:04:45,458
I KNOW THESE LAST FEW DAYS
HAVE BEEN VERY TROUBLING.

103
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:46,625
- TROUBLING?

104
00:04:46,667 --> 00:04:48,208
TROUBLING IS WHEN I GET
THAT ITCHY RASH

105
00:04:48,250 --> 00:04:49,500
THAT WON'T GO AWAY,

106
00:04:49,542 --> 00:04:50,834
AND ZHU LI'S NOT AROUND
TO SCRATCH IT.

107
00:04:50,875 --> 00:04:53,417
THIS IS SHOCKING.
NAY, SICKENING!

108
00:04:53,458 --> 00:04:55,375
BUT THESE KALE COOKIES?
OPPOSITE.

109
00:04:55,417 --> 00:04:58,166
REMIND ME TO GET
THE RECIPE LATER.

110
00:04:58,208 --> 00:04:59,792
- WHAT'S YOUR POINT, VARRICK?

111
00:04:59,834 --> 00:05:01,500
- MY POINT IS,

112
00:05:01,542 --> 00:05:02,917
UNALAQ'S ALREADY BOOTED
OUR CHIEFTAINS

113
00:05:02,959 --> 00:05:04,500
OUT OF THEIR PALACE.

114
00:05:04,542 --> 00:05:05,667
HOW LONG BEFORE HE STARTS
TELLING US

115
00:05:05,709 --> 00:05:07,291
WHAT KIND OF COOKIES
WE CAN EAT?

116
00:05:07,333 --> 00:05:09,125
- PROBABLY A COUPLE OF DAYS.

117
00:05:09,166 --> 00:05:11,542
- RHETORICAL QUESTION, ZHU LI.
YOU GOTTA KEEP UP.

118
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:13,583
NOT TO MENTION I'VE GOT
A CARGO SHIP FULL OF HALIBUT

119
00:05:13,625 --> 00:05:16,041
THAT'S ROTTING,
THANKS TO THIS HARBOR LOCKDOWN.

120
00:05:16,083 --> 00:05:18,500
WHO WANTS TO BUY A SHIP FULL
OF STINKING FISH?

121
00:05:18,542 --> 00:05:20,667
[plate shatters]

122
00:05:20,709 --> 00:05:23,375
SERIOUSLY, IT'S NOT RHETORICAL.
I NEED TO SELL THESE FISH.

123
00:05:23,417 --> 00:05:25,709
- CHIEF UNALAQ IS HERE
TO HELP THE SOUTH.

124
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:27,291
HE WANTS TO SHOW US
HOW TO RESTORE BALANCE

125
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:29,041
WITH THE SPIRITS
SO THEY'LL STOP ATTACKING.

126
00:05:29,083 --> 00:05:32,083
- THE ONLY SPIRIT
I'M INTERESTED IN RESTORING

127
00:05:32,125 --> 00:05:33,834
IS OUR SPIRIT OF INDEPENDENCE!

128
00:05:33,875 --> 00:05:34,917
AM I RIGHT, PEOPLE?

129
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:37,458
[all shouting in agreement]

130
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:39,333
- ALL UNALAQ IS TRYING TO DO

131
00:05:39,375 --> 00:05:41,417
IS MAKE OUR TRIBES
UNIFIED AGAIN.

132
00:05:41,458 --> 00:05:45,291
- NO, HE WANTS CONTROL
OF OUR WEALTH.

133
00:05:45,333 --> 00:05:48,709
MY WEALTH.
AND I LIKE MY WEALTH.

134
00:05:48,750 --> 00:05:50,500
IF UNALAQ DOESN'T PULL
HIS FORCES OUT,

135
00:05:50,542 --> 00:05:53,333
THEN WE HAVE NO CHOICE
BUT TO FIGHT FOR OUR FREEDOM!

136
00:05:53,375 --> 00:05:54,500
[all shouting in agreement]

137
00:05:54,542 --> 00:05:57,291
- YOU WANT TO START A WAR?
ARE YOU CRAZY?

138
00:05:57,333 --> 00:06:00,583
- UNALAQ STARTED THIS,
NOT US.

139
00:06:00,625 --> 00:06:02,041
[sighs]

140
00:06:02,083 --> 00:06:03,917
I'M SORRY.

141
00:06:03,959 --> 00:06:06,291
MAYBE YOU COULD SPEAK
WITH YOUR UNCLE.

142
00:06:06,333 --> 00:06:08,917
TELL HIM HOW FRUSTRATED
WE ALL ARE.

143
00:06:08,959 --> 00:06:11,792
HE'LL LISTEN TO WHAT
THE AVATAR HAS TO SAY.

144
00:06:11,834 --> 00:06:13,709
DO IT FOR ME.

145
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:16,917
- I'LL DO IT FOR THE TRIBE.

146
00:06:16,959 --> 00:06:18,458
[door slams]

147
00:06:18,500 --> 00:06:21,375
- I CANNOT STOP EATING
THESE THINGS.

148
00:06:21,417 --> 00:06:23,792
LOOK, WE ALL KNOW
WHERE THIS CONFLICT IS HEADING.

149
00:06:23,834 --> 00:06:27,917
WE NEED TO START PREPARING
FOR WAR.

150
00:06:27,959 --> 00:06:30,500
- [panting]

151
00:06:30,542 --> 00:06:32,542
- I WILL HATE TO LEAVE
THIS QUAINT TRIBE.

152
00:06:32,583 --> 00:06:35,125
- IS THAT TRUE, ESKA?

153
00:06:35,166 --> 00:06:37,250
- OF COURSE NOT, DESNA.
I WILL NOT MISS IT AT ALL.

154
00:06:37,291 --> 00:06:39,709
I HOLD IMMENSE DISLIKE
FOR THE SOUTH.

155
00:06:39,750 --> 00:06:43,000
[weird, forced laughter]

156
00:06:43,041 --> 00:06:45,083
BOLIN!
LAUGH AT MY HUMOROUS QUIP.

157
00:06:45,125 --> 00:06:47,375
- YES, DEAR.
[awkward laughter]

158
00:06:47,417 --> 00:06:49,458
SO--SO FUNNY.

159
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:52,166
[people chattering]

160
00:06:52,208 --> 00:06:56,542
[grunting]

161
00:06:56,583 --> 00:06:58,667
YOU KNOW,
I'LL BE REALLY SAD

162
00:06:58,709 --> 00:07:00,250
WHEN YOU HAVE TO LEAVE.

163
00:07:00,291 --> 00:07:02,750
IT'S BEEN REALLY GREAT
GETTING TO KNOW YOU.

164
00:07:02,792 --> 00:07:04,125
[chuckles]
REALLY.

165
00:07:04,166 --> 00:07:07,000
- BUT YOU WILL BE COMING
WITH ME TO THE NORTH.

166
00:07:07,041 --> 00:07:08,917
THERE WE WILL LIVE
THE REST OF OUR LIVES TOGETHER

167
00:07:08,959 --> 00:07:10,959
IN ICY BLISS.

168
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:13,083
FOOLISH BOLIN.

169
00:07:13,125 --> 00:07:15,417
- MAKO!
I'M SO HAPPY TO SEE YOU!

170
00:07:15,458 --> 00:07:16,875
- UH, YOU ALL RIGHT, BRO?

171
00:07:16,917 --> 00:07:18,083
- NO!
NO, I'M NOT ALL RIGHT!

172
00:07:18,125 --> 00:07:19,625
I CAN'T TAKE ANYMORE.

173
00:07:19,667 --> 00:07:22,041
LISTEN, I DON'T WANT TO LIVE
IN ICY BLISS WITH ESKA!

174
00:07:22,083 --> 00:07:23,709
[sobbing]
DON'T MAKE ME!

175
00:07:23,750 --> 00:07:26,000
OH, PLEASE,
PLEASE DON'T MAKE ME.

176
00:07:26,041 --> 00:07:27,792
- UH, HEY,
IF YOU'RE THAT UNHAPPY,

177
00:07:27,834 --> 00:07:29,542
JUST BREAK UP WITH HER.

178
00:07:29,583 --> 00:07:31,667
- BREAK UP WITH HER?
YOU CAN DO THAT?

179
00:07:31,709 --> 00:07:33,125
- YEAH.
GUYS DO IT ALL THE TIME.

180
00:07:33,166 --> 00:07:34,959
- HOW?

181
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,458
- JUST TELL HER YOU'RE NOT
THAT INTO HER ANYMORE.

182
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:38,500
- OH, NO, NO, I DON'T THINK
SHE'D LIKE THAT.

183
00:07:38,542 --> 00:07:40,208
- ENDING A RELATIONSHIP
IS KIND OF LIKE

184
00:07:40,250 --> 00:07:42,291
PULLING OFF
A BLOODSUCKING LEECH.

185
00:07:42,333 --> 00:07:44,166
YOU JUST GOTTA RIP IT OFF
AND GET IT OVER WITH.

186
00:07:44,208 --> 00:07:45,834
YOU'LL FEEL A LOT BETTER
AFTERWARDS.

187
00:07:45,875 --> 00:07:47,291
TRUST ME.

188
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:49,375
- THANKS, MAKO.
WHEW.

189
00:07:49,417 --> 00:07:51,250
I'M LUCKY YOU'RE SO GOOD
AT BREAKING GIRLS' HEARTS.

190
00:07:51,291 --> 00:07:53,291
[laughs]
KORRA BETTER WATCH OUT.

191
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:56,208
OOH, NO, IT'S JUST A--

192
00:07:56,250 --> 00:07:58,959
UH, YOU KN--
UH, NEVER MIND.

193
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:01,959
[mystical music]

194
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:05,000
♪ ♪

195
00:08:05,041 --> 00:08:07,041
[footsteps approach]

196
00:08:07,083 --> 00:08:09,417
- OUR NEXT TRAINING SESSION
ISN'T UNTIL TOMORROW.

197
00:08:09,458 --> 00:08:12,041
- I'M SORRY TO INTERRUPT.

198
00:08:12,083 --> 00:08:14,041
IT'S ABOUT OUR CONVERSATION
THIS MORNING.

199
00:08:14,083 --> 00:08:15,792
- YES?

200
00:08:15,834 --> 00:08:17,458
- I UNDERSTAND WHY
YOU BROUGHT YOUR TROOPS HERE,

201
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:19,959
BUT I'M AFRAID IT'S SENDING
THE WRONG MESSAGE.

202
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,083
- YOUR FATHER HAS BEEN TALKING
TO YOU.

203
00:08:22,125 --> 00:08:24,500
- NOT JUST HIM.
VARRICK TOO.

204
00:08:24,542 --> 00:08:26,667
THERE WAS A MEETING
AT MY PARENTS' HOUSE.

205
00:08:26,709 --> 00:08:28,667
A LOT OF SOUTHERNERS FEEL
LIKE THEIR TRIBE

206
00:08:28,709 --> 00:08:30,166
IS BEING INVADED.

207
00:08:30,208 --> 00:08:32,166
- I AM THEIR CHIEF.

208
00:08:32,208 --> 00:08:34,834
I'M UNITING,
NOT INVADING.

209
00:08:34,875 --> 00:08:38,333
- I KNOW, BUT I'M JUST AFRAID
IF SOMETHING DOESN'T CHANGE,

210
00:08:38,375 --> 00:08:40,583
THERE COULD BE
A CIVIL WAR.

211
00:08:40,625 --> 00:08:42,709
- IF THE WATER TRIBES
WERE AT WAR,

212
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:45,041
THE OTHER NATIONS
WOULD TAKE SIDES.

213
00:08:45,083 --> 00:08:48,125
THE DARK SPIRITS WOULD THRIVE
OFF THIS NEGATIVE ENERGY,

214
00:08:48,166 --> 00:08:49,709
AND THE WORLD WOULD BE THROWN
INTO A BATTLE

215
00:08:49,750 --> 00:08:51,333
BETWEEN SPIRITS AND MAN.

216
00:08:51,375 --> 00:08:53,083
THAT WOULD BE CATASTROPHIC.

217
00:08:53,125 --> 00:08:55,500
- HOW DO WE STOP IT?
- WE?

218
00:08:55,542 --> 00:08:57,458
NO, KORRA.

219
00:08:57,500 --> 00:09:00,250
THIS IS A WAR ONLY THE AVATAR
CAN PREVENT.

220
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:07,166
- I'M USUALLY THE ONE
STARTING FIGHTS.

221
00:09:07,208 --> 00:09:09,000
I DON'T KNOW HOW TO STOP THEM
FROM HAPPENING.

222
00:09:09,041 --> 00:09:11,500
- AS THE AVATAR,
YOU MUST REMAIN NEUTRAL

223
00:09:11,542 --> 00:09:12,959
IN THIS CONFLICT.

224
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:15,125
YOU WILL NATURALLY WANT
TO HELP YOUR PEOPLE,

225
00:09:15,166 --> 00:09:17,417
BUT SHOWING FAVORITISM
WILL NOT HELP OUR TRIBES

226
00:09:17,458 --> 00:09:19,166
FIND UNITY.

227
00:09:19,208 --> 00:09:21,208
- MAYBE TENZIN WAS RIGHT.

228
00:09:21,250 --> 00:09:23,208
MAYBE I'M NOT READY
TO BE THE AVATAR.

229
00:09:23,250 --> 00:09:25,125
- TENZIN LACKED FAITH IN YOU.

230
00:09:25,166 --> 00:09:27,291
BUT I HAVE NO DOUBT
YOU WILL BECOME

231
00:09:27,333 --> 00:09:30,166
THE MOST ADMIRED AVATAR
THE WORLD HAS EVER KNOWN.

232
00:09:30,208 --> 00:09:32,166
- THANK YOU, UNCLE.

233
00:09:32,208 --> 00:09:34,125
[people chattering]

234
00:09:47,041 --> 00:09:48,125
- WHO THREW THOSE?

235
00:09:48,166 --> 00:09:49,583
[kids laughing]

236
00:09:49,625 --> 00:09:51,458
[air whooshes]

237
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:54,583
[kids scream]

238
00:09:54,625 --> 00:09:56,583
YOU HOODLUMS THINK
YOU'RE TOUGH, HUH?

239
00:09:56,625 --> 00:09:58,333
- PICK ON A WATERBENDER
YOUR OWN SIZE!

240
00:09:58,375 --> 00:10:01,542
[water splashing]

241
00:10:01,583 --> 00:10:04,333
- STOP!

242
00:10:04,375 --> 00:10:06,250
- TELL THESE THUGS
TO GO BACK TO THE NORTH.

243
00:10:06,291 --> 00:10:07,792
THEY'RE NOT WELCOME HERE
ANYMORE!

244
00:10:07,834 --> 00:10:10,000
- THESE SOUTHERNERS
NEED TO STAY IN LINE.

245
00:10:10,041 --> 00:10:11,625
- EVERYONE, CALM DOWN.

246
00:10:11,667 --> 00:10:13,291
YOU'RE ALL PART
OF THE SAME TRIBE.

247
00:10:13,333 --> 00:10:14,417
START ACTING LIKE IT.

248
00:10:14,458 --> 00:10:16,208
- YOU'RE TAKING THEIR SIDE?

249
00:10:16,250 --> 00:10:17,792
WE THOUGHT YOU WERE
ONE OF US.

250
00:10:17,834 --> 00:10:19,500
- I'M NOT TAKING
ANYONE'S SIDE.

251
00:10:19,542 --> 00:10:20,667
HEY!

252
00:10:20,709 --> 00:10:23,375
- YOU'RE THE WORST AVATAR EVER!

253
00:10:25,792 --> 00:10:30,542
- EVERYONE, WALK AWAY
FROM THIS.

254
00:10:30,583 --> 00:10:32,417
THEY'RE NOT WORTH OUR TROUBLE.

255
00:10:32,458 --> 00:10:35,333
GO BACK TO YOUR HOMES.

256
00:10:45,208 --> 00:10:48,208
KORRA, I--

257
00:10:48,250 --> 00:10:51,166
KORRA!

258
00:10:55,375 --> 00:10:57,583
- IKKI!

259
00:10:57,625 --> 00:11:01,542
IKKI!

260
00:11:01,583 --> 00:11:03,667
IKKI?

261
00:11:03,709 --> 00:11:06,291
IKKI, WHERE ARE YOU?

262
00:11:06,333 --> 00:11:09,083
- [childlike voice]
OVER HERE, DAD!

263
00:11:09,125 --> 00:11:11,542
[laughs]
JUST KIDDING. IT'S ME!

264
00:11:11,583 --> 00:11:13,792
- [groans]

265
00:11:13,834 --> 00:11:15,500
- THERE'S NO SIGN
OF HER ANYWHERE.

266
00:11:15,542 --> 00:11:18,041
- WHY WOULD IKKI
RUN OFF LIKE THIS?

267
00:11:18,083 --> 00:11:19,792
AH, IT'S PROBABLY MY FAULT.

268
00:11:19,834 --> 00:11:22,000
- PROBABLY.
- EXCUSE ME?

269
00:11:22,041 --> 00:11:23,583
- I'M GUESSING YOU'VE BEEN
SO BUSY

270
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:25,583
WITH YOUR "DUTY"
TO REPUBLIC CITY

271
00:11:25,625 --> 00:11:27,583
THAT YOU FORGOT ABOUT YOUR DUTY
TO YOUR KIDS.

272
00:11:27,625 --> 00:11:29,625
- [laughs]
DUTY.

273
00:11:29,667 --> 00:11:31,792
- WHAT ARE YOU,
FIVE YEARS OLD?

274
00:11:31,834 --> 00:11:33,458
- KYA, YOU'RE RIGHT.

275
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:35,333
I HAVEN'T BEEN SPENDING
ENOUGH TIME WITH THEM.

276
00:11:35,375 --> 00:11:36,792
I WISH I COULD BE
AS GOOD A FATHER

277
00:11:36,834 --> 00:11:39,000
AS DAD WAS TO US.

278
00:11:39,041 --> 00:11:42,625
- TENZIN, YOUR PROBLEM IS
YOU'RE EXACTLY LIKE DAD.

279
00:11:42,667 --> 00:11:45,166
HE WAS SO FOCUSED
ON SAVING THE WORLD

280
00:11:45,208 --> 00:11:47,041
AND DOING HIS DUTY--
DON'T LAUGH--

281
00:11:47,083 --> 00:11:49,250
THAT HE NEVER HAD TIME
FOR US.

282
00:11:49,291 --> 00:11:50,667
- DAD WAS UNDER A LOT
OF PRESSURE.

283
00:11:50,709 --> 00:11:53,208
- HE ALWAYS HAD TIME
FOR YOU, THOUGH,

284
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:55,625
HIS PRECIOUS LITTLE AIRBENDER.

285
00:11:55,667 --> 00:11:58,417
- DAD LOVED US ALL EQUALLY.

286
00:11:58,458 --> 00:12:01,250
BESIDES, IT ALL HAPPENED
A LONG TIME AGO.

287
00:12:01,291 --> 00:12:03,000
WHY ARE WE EVEN TALKING
ABOUT THIS?

288
00:12:03,041 --> 00:12:06,041
- BECAUSE YOU SEEM TO HAVE
SOME GRANDIOSE DELUSION

289
00:12:06,083 --> 00:12:08,458
THAT WE HAD A PERFECT,
HAPPY-GO-LUCKY CHILDHOOD.

290
00:12:08,500 --> 00:12:10,125
GUESS WHAT.
WE DIDN'T.

291
00:12:10,166 --> 00:12:11,709
- WE NEED TO KEEP MOVING

292
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:13,458
IF WE WANT TO FIND IKKI
BEFORE DARK.

293
00:12:13,500 --> 00:12:15,250
- SEE WHAT HE'S DOING
THERE, BUMI?

294
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:17,750
CLASSIC AIRBENDER TECHNIQUE.

295
00:12:17,792 --> 00:12:19,625
CUTTING AND RUNNING
WHEN THINGS GET TOUGH!

296
00:12:19,667 --> 00:12:20,667
- UGH.

297
00:12:20,709 --> 00:12:21,875
- YEAH.
DID DAD TEACH YOU THAT MOVE?

298
00:12:21,917 --> 00:12:23,834
[laughs]

299
00:12:27,250 --> 00:12:28,875
- HOW WAS YOUR DAY, SWEETIE?

300
00:12:28,917 --> 00:12:30,709
- OH, FABULOUS.

301
00:12:30,750 --> 00:12:31,834
MY TRIBE'S
ABOUT TO GO TO WAR,

302
00:12:31,875 --> 00:12:33,291
AND I'M SUPPOSED
TO STOP IT,

303
00:12:33,333 --> 00:12:35,166
BUT WILL ANYONE LISTEN
TO ME?

304
00:12:35,208 --> 00:12:37,792
NO! AND I DIDN'T ASK
FOR MY FATHER'S HELP.

305
00:12:37,834 --> 00:12:39,834
CAN'T HE JUST LET ME BE
THE AVATAR?

306
00:12:39,875 --> 00:12:42,375
- UH, DO YOU WANT ADVICE,

307
00:12:42,417 --> 00:12:44,208
OR AM I JUST SUPPOSED
TO LISTEN?

308
00:12:44,250 --> 00:12:45,709
I'M STILL NOT CLEAR ON THAT.

309
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:48,834
- UGH. I'M SORRY.

310
00:12:48,875 --> 00:12:51,083
MY DAD JUST GETS ME
ALL WORKED UP.

311
00:12:51,125 --> 00:12:52,917
- HOW ABOUT YOU TAKE A BREAK
FROM ALL THIS AVATAR STUFF,

312
00:12:52,959 --> 00:12:54,959
AND WE GO OUT
FOR A QUIET DINNER?

313
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:56,041
JUST THE TWO OF US.

314
00:12:56,083 --> 00:12:59,083
[magical music]

315
00:12:59,125 --> 00:13:02,792
♪ ♪

316
00:13:02,834 --> 00:13:04,792
- [laughs awkwardly]
ISN'T THIS FUN, HUH?

317
00:13:04,834 --> 00:13:07,291
WE NEVER GET TO SPEND
ENOUGH TIME TOGETHER,

318
00:13:07,333 --> 00:13:10,333
JUST THE FIVE OF US.

319
00:13:10,375 --> 00:13:13,041
SO FUN.

320
00:13:13,083 --> 00:13:15,750
- EXCUSE US WHILE WE RETRIEVE
MORE SUSTENANCE.

321
00:13:20,458 --> 00:13:21,750
- YOU GUYS GOTTA SAVE ME.

322
00:13:21,792 --> 00:13:23,834
- I THOUGHT YOU WERE
BREAKING UP WITH HER.

323
00:13:23,875 --> 00:13:25,542
WHAT HAPPENED
TO RIPPING OFF THE LEECH?

324
00:13:25,583 --> 00:13:26,834
- I TRIED!

325
00:13:26,875 --> 00:13:28,166
BUT ANYTIME I BRING UP
THE SUBJECT,

326
00:13:28,208 --> 00:13:29,709
SHE THREATENS TO FREEZE ME
IN A BLOCK OF ICE

327
00:13:29,750 --> 00:13:32,375
AND FEED ME
TO DOLPHIN-PIRANHAS!

328
00:13:32,417 --> 00:13:34,166
- SO IT WAS MORE LIKE
YOU TUGGED AT THE LEECH.

329
00:13:34,208 --> 00:13:37,417
- YES, OVER AND OVER AND OVER,
BUT IT WON'T COME OFF.

330
00:13:37,458 --> 00:13:39,291
WHY DIDN'T YOU WARN ME
YOUR COUSIN HAD THE POWER

331
00:13:39,333 --> 00:13:40,667
TO REACH INTO MY HEART
AND CRUSH MY SOUL

332
00:13:40,709 --> 00:13:42,250
WITH HER BARE HANDS?

333
00:13:42,291 --> 00:13:44,792
- UH, 'CAUSE I THOUGHT
IT WAS PRETTY OBVIOUS.

334
00:13:44,834 --> 00:13:46,041
- NO, NO,
NOT TO ME, IT WASN'T.

335
00:13:46,083 --> 00:13:47,583
I'M VERY BAD
AT READING PEOPLE.

336
00:13:47,625 --> 00:13:49,250
YOU SHOULD KNOW THAT
BY NOW.

337
00:13:49,291 --> 00:13:51,709
[sobs]
OH, MAN.

338
00:13:51,750 --> 00:13:53,166
OH!

339
00:13:53,208 --> 00:13:55,792
DO SOMETHING, AVATAR!

340
00:13:55,834 --> 00:13:57,333
- YOU KNOW,
THIS REMINDS ME

341
00:13:57,375 --> 00:13:58,500
OF A SEARCH-AND-RESCUE
MISSION

342
00:13:58,542 --> 00:14:00,667
I COMMANDED YEARS AGO,

343
00:14:00,709 --> 00:14:03,375
IN THE MOUNTAINS
OUTSIDE OF BA SING SE.

344
00:14:03,417 --> 00:14:05,125
- [groans]
HERE WE GO.

345
00:14:05,166 --> 00:14:08,834
- FOR FIVE DAYS, WE SCOURED
THAT BEAST OF A MOUNTAIN,

346
00:14:08,875 --> 00:14:11,583
FIGHTING OUR WAY
THROUGH BLIZZARDS, SANDSTORMS,

347
00:14:11,625 --> 00:14:14,083
AND THREE TYPHOONS.

348
00:14:14,125 --> 00:14:16,041
FINALLY, WE FOUND THE MEN
HUDDLED IN A CAVE,

349
00:14:16,083 --> 00:14:17,458
SECONDS FROM DEATH.

350
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:19,500
WITH NO TIME TO LOSE,

351
00:14:19,542 --> 00:14:22,834
I PILED ALL 12 OF THOSE
POOR SOULS ON MY BACK

352
00:14:22,875 --> 00:14:25,667
AND SINGLE-HANDEDLY
CARRIED THEM

353
00:14:25,709 --> 00:14:27,917
DOWN THE MOUNTAIN
TO SAFETY.

354
00:14:27,959 --> 00:14:31,208
- AND HOW EXACTLY IS THAT
SUPPOSED TO HELP US FIND IKKI?

355
00:14:31,250 --> 00:14:34,000
- IT WAS SUPPOSED
TO INSPIRE YOU.

356
00:14:34,041 --> 00:14:37,208
CLEARLY, YOU KNOW NOTHING
ABOUT BEING A LEADER OF MEN.

357
00:14:37,250 --> 00:14:40,000
THAT'S PROBABLY WHY
THE AVATAR FIRED YOU.

358
00:14:40,041 --> 00:14:42,417
- I'M SICK
OF YOUR FAR-FETCHED TALES.

359
00:14:42,458 --> 00:14:44,208
THREE TYPHOONS?

360
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:46,750
- WELL, I MAY HAVE THROWN IN
AN EXTRA TYPHOON OR TWO

361
00:14:46,792 --> 00:14:48,834
FOR DRAMATIC EFFECT, BUT--

362
00:14:48,875 --> 00:14:50,625
- QUIT ARGUING AND BRING
THAT LANTERN OVER HERE.

363
00:14:50,667 --> 00:14:53,583
I FOUND FOOTPRINTS!

364
00:14:56,458 --> 00:14:59,000
- COME ON!
- NO, FOLLOW ME!

365
00:14:59,041 --> 00:15:03,750
THIS WILL GET US DOWN
50 TIMES FASTER.

366
00:15:03,792 --> 00:15:06,208
- BUMI, IT'S PITCH BLACK,
AND THE ROCKS ARE SLIPPERY.

367
00:15:06,250 --> 00:15:07,333
YOU'RE GONNA HURT YOURSELF.

368
00:15:07,375 --> 00:15:09,417
- COME ON, YOU WIMPS!

369
00:15:09,458 --> 00:15:11,458
IF I CAN DO IT,
IT SHOULD BE NO PROBLEM

370
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:13,041
FOR A COUPLE OF BENDERS.

371
00:15:13,083 --> 00:15:14,959
- FINE.

372
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:17,959
[dramatic music]

373
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:23,166
♪ ♪

374
00:15:23,208 --> 00:15:26,834
- [growls]

375
00:15:26,875 --> 00:15:30,041
- YOU WERE RIGHT, BUMI!
THAT WAS FASTER!

376
00:15:30,083 --> 00:15:33,166
- AT LEAST 50 TIMES FASTER,
BY MY CALCULATIONS.

377
00:15:33,208 --> 00:15:35,208
both: [laughing]

378
00:15:35,250 --> 00:15:38,291
- OH, TENZIN'S
THE FUNNY GUY NOW.

379
00:15:38,333 --> 00:15:41,041
- IF YOU NEED AN AIRLIFT DOWN,
JUST SAY THE WORD.

380
00:15:41,083 --> 00:15:42,709
- BAH, I DON'T NEED YOUR HELP.

381
00:15:42,750 --> 00:15:44,291
I'VE GOT EVERYTHING
UNDER CONTROL.

382
00:15:44,333 --> 00:15:45,291
AGH!

383
00:15:45,333 --> 00:15:48,333
[grunting, screaming]

384
00:15:48,375 --> 00:15:51,291
- BUMI!

385
00:15:57,041 --> 00:15:59,083
- DID DAD SEND YOU
TO TALK TO ME?

386
00:15:59,125 --> 00:16:00,917
- YOUR FATHER DOESN'T KNOW
I'M HERE.

387
00:16:00,959 --> 00:16:03,083
KORRA, WHAT'S GOING ON
BETWEEN YOU TWO?

388
00:16:03,125 --> 00:16:04,667
- ASK DAD.

389
00:16:04,709 --> 00:16:07,291
- I'VE TRIED,
BUT HE WON'T TALK ABOUT IT.

390
00:16:07,333 --> 00:16:09,834
HONEY, IT BREAKS MY HEART
TO SEE OUR FAMILY

391
00:16:09,875 --> 00:16:11,667
BEING TORN APART LIKE THIS.

392
00:16:11,709 --> 00:16:13,792
- YOU WANT TO KNOW
WHAT'S BEEN GOING ON?

393
00:16:13,834 --> 00:16:15,834
I FOUND OUT DAD'S
BEEN LYING TO ME

394
00:16:15,875 --> 00:16:17,667
MY WHOLE LIFE.

395
00:16:17,709 --> 00:16:19,208
UNALAQ TOLD ME EVERYTHING--

396
00:16:19,250 --> 00:16:21,291
HOW DAD AND TENZIN
KEPT ME TRAPPED DOWN HERE

397
00:16:21,333 --> 00:16:22,667
WHILE I TRAINED,

398
00:16:22,709 --> 00:16:26,166
HOW DAD GOT BANISHED
FROM THE NORTH.

399
00:16:26,208 --> 00:16:28,166
- SO THE TRUTH IS OUT.

400
00:16:28,208 --> 00:16:30,166
- YOU KNEW.

401
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:31,834
AND YOU NEVER SAID ANYTHING.

402
00:16:31,875 --> 00:16:34,500
- WE WERE TRYING TO KEEP
OUR FAMILY TOGETHER,

403
00:16:34,542 --> 00:16:36,166
TO GIVE YOU
A NORMAL CHILDHOOD.

404
00:16:36,208 --> 00:16:39,166
- I NEVER WANTED
A NORMAL CHILDHOOD.

405
00:16:39,208 --> 00:16:41,875
ALL I EVER WANTED TO BE
WAS THE AVATAR.

406
00:16:41,917 --> 00:16:43,458
BUT EVERYONE KEEPS
HOLDING ME BACK,

407
00:16:43,500 --> 00:16:44,917
EVEN MY OWN PARENTS!

408
00:16:44,959 --> 00:16:46,709
UNALAQ'S THE ONLY ONE
WHO BELIEVES IN ME.

409
00:16:46,750 --> 00:16:48,417
- THAT'S NOT TRUE, KORRA.

410
00:16:48,458 --> 00:16:50,542
- NO? THEN WHY IS EVERYONE
IN THE SOUTH

411
00:16:50,583 --> 00:16:52,083
TURNING AGAINST ME,
WHEN ALL I'M TRYING TO DO

412
00:16:52,125 --> 00:16:53,458
IS HELP THEM?

413
00:16:53,500 --> 00:16:55,041
- THE PROBLEMS BETWEEN THE NORTH
AND THE SOUTH

414
00:16:55,083 --> 00:16:57,250
STARTED LONG BEFORE YOU
WERE BORN.

415
00:16:57,291 --> 00:16:59,542
YOU CAN'T EXPECT TO UNDO THEM
IN A DAY.

416
00:16:59,583 --> 00:17:01,208
- SO I SHOULD JUST SIT BACK

417
00:17:01,250 --> 00:17:03,208
AND LET THE WATER TRIBES
GO TO WAR?

418
00:17:03,250 --> 00:17:06,875
- NO, BUT THIS SITUATION
MIGHT BE OUT OF YOUR CONTROL.

419
00:17:06,917 --> 00:17:09,834
VARRICK'S BEEN PLOTTING
A REBELLION AGAINST UNALAQ.

420
00:17:09,875 --> 00:17:11,542
HE ASKED YOUR FATHER
TO JOIN, AND--

421
00:17:11,583 --> 00:17:13,333
- DAD IS PART OF A REBELLION?

422
00:17:13,375 --> 00:17:14,875
- I DON'T KNOW,
BUT I DON'T WANT YOU

423
00:17:14,917 --> 00:17:16,250
GETTING CAUGHT
IN THE MIDDLE OF IT.

424
00:17:16,291 --> 00:17:17,792
- IT'S TOO LATE, MOM.

425
00:17:17,834 --> 00:17:20,500
I'M ALREADY
IN THE MIDDLE OF IT.

426
00:17:23,333 --> 00:17:26,250
- KORRA!

427
00:17:30,792 --> 00:17:33,125
- UNCLE!

428
00:17:33,166 --> 00:17:35,333
OH, NO.

429
00:17:35,375 --> 00:17:36,542
UNCLE?

430
00:17:36,583 --> 00:17:39,458
[suspenseful music]

431
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:46,750
♪ ♪

432
00:17:46,792 --> 00:17:47,792
DAD?

433
00:17:53,583 --> 00:17:56,500
- DAD, DON'T DO THIS.

434
00:17:56,542 --> 00:17:58,375
- TURN AROUND, AVATAR,

435
00:17:58,417 --> 00:17:59,834
AND PRETEND YOU DIDN'T SEE
ANYTHING.

436
00:17:59,875 --> 00:18:03,083
- NO. LEAVE UNALAQ AND GO.

437
00:18:03,125 --> 00:18:04,959
I'LL TELL HIM I TRIED
TO STOP YOU, BUT YOU ESCAPED.

438
00:18:05,000 --> 00:18:06,542
WE CAN STILL AVOID A WAR.

439
00:18:06,583 --> 00:18:09,792
- NO, WE CAN'T.

440
00:18:09,834 --> 00:18:12,792
[dramatic music]

441
00:18:12,834 --> 00:18:15,375
♪ ♪

442
00:18:15,417 --> 00:18:17,875
- [grunts]

443
00:18:24,291 --> 00:18:27,208
- GET HIM OUT OF HERE!

444
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:28,917
- [grunts]

445
00:18:28,959 --> 00:18:30,625
WE'RE ALL PART
OF THE SAME TRIBE.

446
00:18:30,667 --> 00:18:33,333
I DON'T WANT TO HURT YOU.

447
00:18:44,458 --> 00:18:46,834
[soldiers gasp and scream]

448
00:18:46,875 --> 00:18:49,208
[soldiers grunt]

449
00:18:54,875 --> 00:18:56,792
[all grunting]

450
00:18:59,333 --> 00:19:00,417
- [screams]

451
00:19:00,458 --> 00:19:04,959
OOF!

452
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:07,667
- DAD, STOP!

453
00:19:16,792 --> 00:19:19,125
- [groans softly]
- WHY DID YOU DO THIS, DAD?

454
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:22,417
[suspenseful music]

455
00:19:22,458 --> 00:19:25,500
WHAT? WHO ARE YOU?
WHERE'S MY FATHER?

456
00:19:25,542 --> 00:19:27,250
- HE WOULDN'T HELP US.

457
00:19:27,291 --> 00:19:31,792
HE'S A TRAITOR,
JUST LIKE YOU.

458
00:19:31,834 --> 00:19:33,750
- [groans]

459
00:19:37,417 --> 00:19:38,959
THANK YOU FOR SAVING
MY LIFE.

460
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:41,458
- I'M JUST GLAD
I GOT HERE IN TIME.

461
00:19:41,500 --> 00:19:43,291
- FIND VARRICK.

462
00:19:43,333 --> 00:19:45,083
I WANT HIM TO FREEZE IN PRISON
WITH THE REST

463
00:19:45,125 --> 00:19:48,875
OF THESE TRAITORS.

464
00:19:48,917 --> 00:19:50,583
- WAIT, YOU CAN'T JUST LOCK
THEM AWAY.

465
00:19:50,625 --> 00:19:52,291
THAT WILL ONLY MAKE
THE SOUTH ANGRIER.

466
00:19:52,333 --> 00:19:54,125
- YOU WANT THEM TO GO FREE?

467
00:19:54,166 --> 00:19:55,667
- NO.

468
00:19:55,709 --> 00:19:58,792
BUT LET THEM STAND TRIAL
FOR WHAT THEY DID.

469
00:19:58,834 --> 00:20:03,208
EVERY WATER TRIBE CITIZEN
DESERVES THAT RIGHT.

470
00:20:03,250 --> 00:20:04,875
- VERY WELL.

471
00:20:04,917 --> 00:20:07,500
I WILL RESPECT THE AVATAR'S
WISHES IN THIS MATTER.

472
00:20:07,542 --> 00:20:10,166
- THANK YOU, UNCLE.

473
00:20:10,208 --> 00:20:12,208
- I TOLD YOU
THOSE ROCKS WERE SLIPPERY.

474
00:20:12,250 --> 00:20:13,834
YOU'RE LUCKY
YOU DIDN'T KILL YOURSELF.

475
00:20:13,875 --> 00:20:15,333
- YOU DONE
WITH THE LECTURE, MOM?

476
00:20:15,375 --> 00:20:17,750
- OH, GROW UP.

477
00:20:17,792 --> 00:20:20,208
YOU HAVEN'T CHANGED ONE BIT
SINCE WE WERE KIDS.

478
00:20:20,250 --> 00:20:21,542
YOU'RE STILL TRYING
TO PROVE

479
00:20:21,583 --> 00:20:23,125
YOU CAN DO EVERYTHING
A BENDER CAN.

480
00:20:23,166 --> 00:20:25,208
WELL, YOU CAN'T.
DEAL WITH IT.

481
00:20:25,250 --> 00:20:27,166
- AND YOU'RE NOT OUR MOTHER.

482
00:20:27,208 --> 00:20:30,625
YOU DON'T GET TO TELL ME
WHAT I CAN AND CAN'T DO.

483
00:20:30,667 --> 00:20:32,500
DEAL WITH THAT.
UGH!

484
00:20:32,542 --> 00:20:33,959
- GOOD LUCK HEALING YOURSELF

485
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:36,041
WITH YOUR SPECIAL
NON-BENDING POWERS.

486
00:20:36,083 --> 00:20:37,917
- HEY, BACK ME UP HERE,
TENZIN.

487
00:20:37,959 --> 00:20:39,458
- KYA'S RIGHT.

488
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:41,125
YOU'RE THE OLDEST OF US,

489
00:20:41,166 --> 00:20:42,959
BUT YOU ALWAYS ACTED
LIKE THE YOUNGEST.

490
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,208
I HAD TO BECOME
THE RESPONSIBLE ONE.

491
00:20:45,250 --> 00:20:48,583
- YOU THINK YOU'RE
THE RESPONSIBLE ONE?

492
00:20:48,625 --> 00:20:51,166
WHERE WERE YOU AFTER DAD DIED
AND MOM WAS ALL ALONE?

493
00:20:51,208 --> 00:20:53,834
BECAUSE I WAS THE ONLY ONE
WHO PACKED UP AND MOVED

494
00:20:53,875 --> 00:20:55,917
MY WHOLE LIFE
TO BE WITH HER.

495
00:20:55,959 --> 00:20:57,583
- SURE, AFTER YEARS
OF FLITTING AROUND THE WORLD,

496
00:20:57,625 --> 00:21:00,125
TRYING TO FIND YOURSELF.

497
00:21:00,166 --> 00:21:02,333
IT WAS TIME FOR YOU
TO SETTLE DOWN SOMEWHERE.

498
00:21:02,375 --> 00:21:04,875
YOU TWO HAVE NO IDEA
HOW IT FEELS TO HAVE THE FUTURE

499
00:21:04,917 --> 00:21:06,959
OF AN ENTIRE CULTURE
ON YOUR SHOULDERS.

500
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:08,250
- OH, BOO-HOO.

501
00:21:08,291 --> 00:21:09,834
MUST'VE BEEN REAL HARD
FOR YOU,

502
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:11,417
FLYING AROUND THE WORLD
WITH DAD,

503
00:21:11,458 --> 00:21:13,083
RIDING ELEPHANT-KOI ALL DAY.

504
00:21:13,125 --> 00:21:15,542
- OH, SO THAT'S WHAT THIS
IS ALL ABOUT.

505
00:21:15,583 --> 00:21:17,792
- THAT'S WHAT IT'S ALWAYS
BEEN ABOUT.

506
00:21:17,834 --> 00:21:19,792
YOU THINK YOU'RE SOME SAVIOR

507
00:21:19,834 --> 00:21:21,917
WHO HAS TO CARRY ON
DAD'S LEGACY.

508
00:21:21,959 --> 00:21:23,417
- WHO ELSE IS GOING TO DO IT?

509
00:21:23,458 --> 00:21:24,917
- HOW ABOUT ALL OF US?

510
00:21:24,959 --> 00:21:27,333
- YEAH, WE'RE AANG'S KIDS TOO.

511
00:21:27,375 --> 00:21:29,542
- WE NEVER SHOULD HAVE COME
ON THIS VACATION.

512
00:21:29,583 --> 00:21:31,500
- I COULDN'T AGREE MORE.

513
00:21:31,542 --> 00:21:33,875
- WELL, I DIDN'T WANT YOU
TO COME IN THE FIRST PLACE.

514
00:21:33,917 --> 00:21:36,208
I CAN'T BE AROUND YOU TWO
RIGHT NOW.

515
00:21:36,250 --> 00:21:38,417
GO BACK TO THE TEMPLE
AND SEE IF IKKI RETURNED.

516
00:21:38,458 --> 00:21:39,375
I'LL KEEP LOOKING OUT HERE.

517
00:21:39,417 --> 00:21:40,917
- FINE.
- FINE.

518
00:21:40,959 --> 00:21:41,959
- FINE.

519
00:21:44,083 --> 00:21:45,750
[owl hooting]

520
00:21:58,542 --> 00:22:00,166
- IS IT OKAY IF I COME IN?

521
00:22:00,208 --> 00:22:02,333
- OF COURSE.
WE HEARD WHAT HAPPENED.

522
00:22:02,375 --> 00:22:04,333
ARE YOU OKAY?

523
00:22:04,375 --> 00:22:07,333
[emotional music]

524
00:22:07,375 --> 00:22:09,333
♪ ♪

525
00:22:09,375 --> 00:22:11,291
- I'M SO GLAD
YOU WEREN'T THERE.

526
00:22:11,333 --> 00:22:12,750
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT I WOULD HAVE DONE.

527
00:22:12,792 --> 00:22:16,959
- I HAD NO IDEA HOW FAR VARRICK
WAS WILLING TO GO.

528
00:22:17,000 --> 00:22:18,375
MY BROTHER AND I
HAVE OUR DIFFERENCES,

529
00:22:18,417 --> 00:22:20,583
BUT I WOULD NEVER ATTACK HIM.

530
00:22:20,625 --> 00:22:22,458
- I'M SORRY FOR THINKING
YOU HAD ANYTHING TO DO

531
00:22:22,500 --> 00:22:24,083
WITH THE REBELS,

532
00:22:24,125 --> 00:22:26,000
AND FOR ALL THE PAIN
I'VE CAUSED YOU AND MOM.

533
00:22:26,041 --> 00:22:28,041
- I'M THE ONE
WHO SHOULD APOLOGIZE.

534
00:22:28,083 --> 00:22:29,709
AFTER I SAW
THE SOUTHERN LIGHTS RETURN,

535
00:22:29,750 --> 00:22:31,542
I WAS SO PROUD OF YOU.

536
00:22:31,583 --> 00:22:34,291
I NEVER SHOULD HAVE HELD
YOU BACK.

537
00:22:34,333 --> 00:22:36,542
- WHEN YOUR FATHER AND I
FOUND EACH OTHER,

538
00:22:36,583 --> 00:22:38,417
ALL WE WANTED WAS TO LIVE
A SIMPLE LIFE

539
00:22:38,458 --> 00:22:40,417
AND RAISE A FAMILY.

540
00:22:40,458 --> 00:22:42,834
BUT THEN WE DISCOVERED
YOU WERE THE AVATAR,

541
00:22:42,875 --> 00:22:44,917
AND SIMPLE WAS OVER.

542
00:22:44,959 --> 00:22:47,208
WE KNEW ONE DAY
THE WORLD WOULD NEED YOU,

543
00:22:47,250 --> 00:22:49,166
AND YOU WOULDN'T NEED US
ANYMORE.

544
00:22:49,208 --> 00:22:51,875
- MOM, DAD,
OF COURSE I STILL NEED YOU.

545
00:22:56,875 --> 00:22:57,917
- WE WEREN'T EXPECTING YOU.

546
00:22:57,959 --> 00:23:00,625
- TONRAQ, SENNA,
YOU ARE UNDER ARREST

547
00:23:00,667 --> 00:23:01,792
AND WILL STAND TRIAL.

548
00:23:01,834 --> 00:23:03,667
- TRIAL? FOR WHAT?

549
00:23:03,709 --> 00:23:06,709
- FOR CONSPIRING
TO ASSASSINATE ME.

550
00:23:06,750 --> 00:23:09,375
[ominous music]
